<paragraph blockId="7.[184,1069,828,1412]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
In 
<bibRefCitation author="Turner, H." box="[212,363,828,852]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" refId="ref2687" refString="Turner, H. (2001): Katalog der Familie Costellariidae MACDONALD 1860 (Gastropoda: Prosobranchia: Muricoidea). - 100 pp., Hackenheim." type="book" year="2001">Turner (2001)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName authority="MELVILLL, 1888" authorityName="MELVILLL" authorityYear="1888" box="[371,720,828,852]" class="Hypotrichea" family="Oxytrichidae" genus="Mitra" kingdom="Chromista" order="Oxytrichida" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="chariessa">
<emphasis box="[371,543,828,852]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Mitra chariessa</emphasis>
MELVILLL, 1888
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[734,798,828,852]" captionStart="Plate 3" captionStartId="5.[184,229,1482,1500]" captionTargetId="figure-12@6.[221,1105,153,1627]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Plate 3: Vexillum (Costellaria) scitulum (A. ADAMS, 1853), all figures 5 x Fig. 6: Syntype 1/2, NHMUK 1967876/1, China Seas, 14.6 mm x 4.7 mm (photo John Wolff). Fig. 7: Syntype 2/2, NHMUK 1967876/2, China Seas, 11.8 mm x 3.8 mm (photo Hans Turner). Fig. 8: Holotype of Mitra chariessa MELVILL, 1888; NMW 1955.158.00392, no locality (photo Harriet Wood, NMW)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846230" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846230/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) was synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="RoDING" authorityYear="1798" box="[184,279,865,889]" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[184,279,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Vexillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="(ADAMS &amp; REEVE, 1850)" baseAuthorityName="ADAMS &amp; REEVE" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[287,712,865,889]" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rubellum" subGenus="Costellaria">
(
<emphasis box="[296,310,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[335,435,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">rubellum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Adams, A. &amp; Reeve, L." box="[453,702,865,889]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" refId="ref2451" refString="Adams, A. &amp; Reeve, L. (1850): Mollusca. - In: A. Adams (ed.): The zoology of the voyage of H. M. S. Samarang under the command of Captain Sir Edward Belcher, C. B., F. R. A. S., F. G. S., during the years 1843 - 1846. 87 pp., 24 plates, London." type="book" year="1850">ADAMS &amp; REEVE, 1850</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[726,838,865,889]" captionStart="Plate 4" captionStartId="7.[184,229,1509,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-12@8.[221,1105,153,1627]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Plate 4: Vexillum (Costellaria) rubellum (ADAMS &amp; REEVE, 1850), all figures 5 x Fig. 9: MH, Philippines, Palawan, Balabac Island, collected 2005, 29.4 mm x 10.0 mm (photo Manfred Herrmann). Fig. 10: Type figure of Mitra rubella ADAMS &amp; REEVE, 1850." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5846233" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5846233/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Figs 9â€“10</figureCitation>
), but when comparing the 
<typeStatus box="[272,323,902,926]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">type</typeStatus>
species in NMW with the new species, the authors realized that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MELVILLL" authorityYear="1888" box="[184,329,940,964]" class="Hypotrichea" family="Oxytrichidae" genus="Mitra" kingdom="Chromista" order="Oxytrichida" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="chariessa">
<emphasis box="[184,329,940,964]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">M. chariessa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be synonymized with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="RoDING" authorityYear="1798" box="[678,775,940,964]" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[678,775,940,964]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">Vexillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="(A. ADAMS, 1853)" baseAuthorityName="A. ADAMS" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scitulum" subGenus="Costellaria">
(
<emphasis box="[794,808,940,964]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[835,932,940,964]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">scitulum</emphasis>
(A. ADAMS, 1853)
</taxonomicName>
instead.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[184,1069,828,1412]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
The type of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MELVILLL" authorityYear="1888" box="[367,517,1014,1038]" class="Hypotrichea" family="Oxytrichidae" genus="Mitra" kingdom="Chromista" order="Oxytrichida" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="chariessa">
<emphasis box="[367,517,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">M. chariessa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the 
<typeStatus box="[627,733,1014,1038]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">syntypes</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[774,788,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">V</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="A. ADAMS" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[805,956,1014,1038]" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scitulum" subGenus="Costellaria">
(
<emphasis box="[815,829,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[857,956,1014,1038]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">scitulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have the same slender appearance, an identical cancellated surface with a more prominent second spiral cord below the suture and the same colouration. The 
<typeStatus box="[938,1038,1089,1113]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MELVILLL" authorityYear="1888" box="[184,329,1126,1150]" class="Hypotrichea" family="Oxytrichidae" genus="Mitra" kingdom="Chromista" order="Oxytrichida" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="species" species="chariessa">
<emphasis box="[184,329,1126,1150]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">M. chariessa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the larger 
<typeStatus box="[509,600,1126,1150]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<emphasis box="[639,652,1126,1150]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">V</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="A. ADAMS" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[668,815,1126,1150]" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="scitulum" subGenus="Costellaria">
(
<emphasis box="[678,692,1126,1150]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[718,815,1126,1150]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">scitulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are nearly completely faded, but on close examination, slightly brown faded dots can be seen on the periphery of the body whorl of both shells. This characteristic can be better seen on the smaller 
<typeStatus box="[410,501,1238,1262]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">syntype</typeStatus>
in the NHMUK.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[184,1069,828,1412]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">
In contrast, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="ADAMS &amp; REEVE" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[355,528,1276,1300]" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rubellum" subGenus="Costellaria">
<emphasis box="[355,368,1276,1300]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">V</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[391,405,1276,1300]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[428,528,1276,1300]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">rubellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from the mentioned 
<typeStatus box="[829,895,1276,1300]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">types</typeStatus>
. This species is larger, the axial ribs are thicker and, as mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Adams, A. &amp; Reeve, L." box="[806,1068,1313,1337]" pageId="7" pageNumber="64" refId="ref2451" refString="Adams, A. &amp; Reeve, L. (1850): Mollusca. - In: A. Adams (ed.): The zoology of the voyage of H. M. S. Samarang under the command of Captain Sir Edward Belcher, C. B., F. R. A. S., F. G. S., during the years 1843 - 1846. 87 pp., 24 plates, London." type="book" year="1850">Adams &amp; Reeve (1850)</bibRefCitation>
in the original description, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="ADAMS &amp; REEVE" baseAuthorityYear="1850" box="[496,676,1350,1374]" class="Gastropoda" family="Costellariidae" genus="Vexillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="7" pageNumber="57" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="rubellum" subGenus="Costellaria">
<emphasis box="[496,509,1350,1374]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">V</emphasis>
. (
<emphasis box="[534,548,1350,1374]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">C</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[574,676,1350,1374]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="64">rubellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has more swollen whorls and the longer siphonal canal is significantly recurved.
</paragraph>
